==Abstract==

This IIP specifies per-commitment key derivation for Lightning channels, adapted from BOLT #3 for ML-DSA-87.

==Specification==

===Key Hierarchy===

<pre>
funding_key (permanent)
    |
    +-- per_commitment_point[n] (per-state)
            |
            +-- local_payment_key
            +-- remote_payment_key
            +-- local_htlc_key
            +-- remote_htlc_key
            +-- local_delayed_payment_key
            +-- revocation_key
</pre>

===Per-Commitment Secrets===

Generate 2^48 unique secrets from a single seed using shachain-like structure for O(log n) storage.

===Key Derivation===

All derivations use SHAKE256:

<pre>
// Payment key
derived_key = KeyGen(SHAKE256(basepoint || per_commitment_point || "payment"))

// Revocation key
revocation_key = KeyGen(SHAKE256(revocation_basepoint ||
                                  per_commitment_point ||
                                  "revocation"))
</pre>

===Dilithium5 Adaptation===

Unlike ECDSA algebraic tweaking, Dilithium5 requires:
# Derive seed from base materials
# Generate new keypair from seed
# '''Both parties must store derived public keys'''

==Security Considerations==

* Per-commitment secrets MUST be stored encrypted
* Base keys MUST be derived from HD wallet seed
* Revealed secrets MUST be persisted for breach remedy

